---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout blankHeader hideFooter>
	<main class="legal-page">
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p>
			LifePattern.AI believes in transparency and honesty, and user privacy is our first priority.
			For concerns, contact <a href="mailto:privacy@lifepattern.ai"><strong><em>privacy@lifepattern.ai</em></strong></a>.
		</p>

		<h2>What information does the application obtain and for what purpose?</h2>
		<p>
			The basic subscription saves all your information on your device. Unless you explicitly ask,
			we do not store or access your entries and data. <strong>By default your data is stored only locally on your device.</strong>
			You can optionally back up data to Google Drive on Android or Apple iCloud on iOS.
		</p>
		<p>
			We obtain your email address when you request support by email or a customer support form.
			We use your email only to provide support, feedback, or important information.
		</p>

		<h2>Backup</h2>
		<p>We recommend regular backups. Users may opt in to a tier that provides backup and sync across devices.</p>
		<p><strong>Android Google Drive Backups</strong></p>
		<p>
			Android users can optionally back up data using Google Drive. Backups are stored in private
			Google Drive space and count against the user's quota. We use a secure connection to the Google
			Account and do not keep email addresses or names inside the app.
			View Google's policy at <a href="https://www.google.com/policies/privacy/">https://www.google.com/policies/privacy/</a>.
		</p>
		<p><strong>iOS iCloud Backups</strong></p>
		<p>
			iOS users can optionally back up data using iCloud Drive. Backups are stored in private iCloud
			Drive space and count against the user's quota. Learn more about iCloud security at
			<a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202303">https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202303</a>.
		</p>

		<h2>Analytics</h2>
		<p>
			The application may collect anonymized usage data that helps us deliver and improve services,
			such as app launches, taps, screen visits, session durations, app updates, or crash and
			performance reports. These data are anonymized and aggregated. The application does
			<strong> not collect </strong> user-generated content such as journal entries, photos, names,
			surnames, email, or anything typed within the app.
		</p>

		<h2>Photos</h2>
		<p>
			You may attach photos to journal entries. Photos are stored locally in app storage. If you
			choose cloud backup, multi-device support, or manual export, photos may be included in those
			private backups or exported files. We have no access to your photos.
		</p>

		<h2>Android and iOS Third-Party Services</h2>
		<p><strong>Google Analytics for Firebase (Google Inc.)</strong></p>
		<ul>
			<li>Used to collect and analyze anonymized usage data to improve the app.</li>
			<li>Data may include device identifiers, installation IDs, usage data, anonymized IP addresses, session durations, device models, operating systems, geography, and app events.</li>
			<li>Data retention: 2 months.</li>
		</ul>
		<p><strong>Firebase Crashlytics (Google Inc.)</strong></p>
		<ul>
			<li>Used to identify crashes and errors to improve app reliability.</li>
			<li>Data may include Crashlytics installation UUIDs, crash traces, device models, geography, and operating systems.</li>
			<li>Data retention: 90 days.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Changes</h2>
		<p>
			We may modify or replace this policy at any time. Changes will be posted on this page, and
			users should review it from time to time.
		</p>

